model_explanation: in S1, the prosodic focus is on "BILL," meaning Sam did not give bananas to anyone else, but it does not say that Bill couldn't receive other things. S2 says Bill also got grapes, which doesn't contradict the focus on the recipient. It contradicts the implied meaning that Bill only got bananas. Therefore, S2 contradicts the meaning of S1.

in S1, the prosodic focus is on "MARY," meaning that Sam did not give apples to anyone else besides Mary. S2 says Sam also gave apples to Ellen, which directly contradicts the meaning of S1 that no one else got apples.
in S1, the prosodic focus is on "SUE," meaning no one else besides Sue received apples. S2 says that Tom also received apples, which directly contradicts the meaning of S1.

in S1, the prosodic focus is on "GRAPES," meaning Bill only received grapes and nothing else. S2 states that Bill didn't receive oranges. This is entailed by S1, as it reinforces that Bill did not get anything other than grapes.

in S1, the prosodic focus is on "APPLES," meaning Bill only received apples and nothing else. S2 states that Bill didn’t get bananas. This is entailed by S1 because it supports the idea that Bill didn’t get anything other than apples.
in S1, the prosodic focus is on "APPLES," meaning Sue only got apples and nothing else. S2 says Sue didn’t get bananas, which is entailed by S1, because it confirms Sue got no other items.

in S1, the prosodic focus is on "ELLEN," meaning Sam gave oranges only to Ellen and no one else. S2 says Tom didn’t get oranges, which is entailed by S1, confirming no one else besides Ellen received oranges.
in S1, the prosodic focus is on "TOM," meaning Sam gave apples only to Tom and no one else. S2 says Mary didn’t get apples, which is entailed by S1, confirming no one besides Tom received apples.
in S1, the prosodic focus is on "TOM," meaning only Tom received apples and no one else did. S2 says that Bill also got apples, which directly contradicts S1’s assertion.

in S1, the prosodic focus is on "SUE," meaning Sam gave bananas only to Sue, and no one else received bananas. S2 says Tom didn’t get bananas, which is entailed by S1. It confirms that no one other than Sue got bananas.
